author: RICK JOLLY
description: Rick Jolly was the Senior Medical Officer in the Falklands, setting up and running the field hospital at Ajax Bay. Rick's diary of the campaign is a fast-paced and gripping account that covers the entire conflict. Incredible stories abound as Rick, a trained commando, saves lives--and risks his own--on a daily basis. Revised and fully updated, this book is a unique firsthand narrative of a conflict that inspired heroism but continues to provoke fierce debate.
